Business Brief -- Marvel Entertainment Group Inc.:
   Publisher of Comic Books
   Expects Earnings to Double
The company said net for the quarter ending March 31
should be $4.1 million, or 34 cents a share, compared with
$1.6 million, or 13 cents a share, last year. Revenue is
expected to be $28 million.
   On the New York Stock Exchange yesterday, Marvel shares
closed up $1.50 at $51.